creator: Various
description:
LibriVox recording of Short Poetry Collection 134 by Various.
Read in English by Ian King; Son of the Exiles; Rosslyn Carlyle; Shakira Searle; Glenn O'Brien; Willy; Leonard Wilson; Kit Noussis
This is a collection of 18 poems read by LibriVox volunteers for July 2014. This collection includes the following: Adlestrop, by Edward Thomas After All, by Henry Lawson Ah, Are You Digging on My Grave?, by Thomas Hardy And You Helen, by Edward Thomas Blue Water, by John Gould Fletcher The Bush Girl, by Henry Lawson Do They Think That I Do Not Know, by Henry Lawson The Hayloft, by Robert Louis Stevenson If We Must Die, by Claude McKay The Man He Killed, by Thomas Hardy Poetry, by Claude McKay Prayers For Wind, by John Gould Fletcher Saltbush Bill's Second Fight, by Andrew Barton "Banjo" Paterson Sonnet V (Once more into my arid days like dew), by Edna St. Vincent Millay Sport, by Hamlin Garland Summer Morn in New Hampshire, by Claude McKay The Swing, by Robert Louis Stevenson The Tyger, by William Blake
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (15MB)
